Knowing several languages, especially those of developing economies, will equip children with a better chance of getting meaningful work.
In Scotland, each school will differ in the languages they teach.
Some schools will focus on the more classical modern languages, while others will teach languages that are deemed essential for the UK when looking ahead to 2020, such as Mandarin or Japanese.
Whatever your child's interest, there will always be a number of languages to choose from in independent schools, with teaching staff who are specialists in this field.
Scottish independent schools are dedicated to providing a learning environment that will prepare children and equip them with the skills needed to achieve success, regardless of what the future holds.
At this stage, in a global business environment, it cannot be denied that languages are still tremendously important for the country's future, and therefore it must be reflected in education.
True, modern languages should really be considered as "international communication skills."
Independent schools will continue to offer this choice, diversity and excellence to Scotland's young people.
We have to do it right.
